<HEADLINE>
Fbl: Mariners take full points off Glory, top A-League
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Central Coast Mariners successfully held on for a 1-0 away win
over Perth Glory on Sunday to maintain a four-point lead at the
top of Australia's A-League.
</P>
<P>
Greg Owens scored the only goal in the 12th minute to maintain
the Central Coast's hold on the top spot.
</P>
<P>
Exciting youngster Robbie Kruse's winner against champions
Melbourne Victory kept Queensland Roar in second place in the
standings.
</P>
<P>
It was an individual piece of goal-scoring brilliance from the
in-form 19-year- old, who pounced on a loose ball in the 10th
minute before beating a defender and curling it into the bottom
corner from the edge of the penalty area.
</P>
<P>
The Roar's third-straight win kept them in second place on 22
points while the Victory have slumped to sixth following their
fourth loss of the season.
</P>
<P>
Newcastle and Adelaide cancelled each other out with second half
goals for a 1-1 draw at Adelaide's Hindmarsh Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Joel Griffiths gave Newcastle Jets hope of a precious road win in
evening heat when he slotted home midway through the second half,
but Travis Dodd answered within minutes to preserve a point and
third spot on the table for the home side.
</P>
<P>
Sydney FC forced a 1-1 draw with Wellington Phoenix in New
Zealand through an injury time penalty from midfielder Ufuk
Talay.
</P>
<P>
Skipper Ross Aloisi had put the Phoenix ahead with a close-range
strike in the 28th minute.
</P>
